caption: I gotta be straight up about the new chicken sandwich.  It’s just not that special.  Sure, it’s a solid piece of chicken that you can actually tear apart with your teeth, but it’s truly not groundbreaking.  In fact, for $5.05 after tax, it’s rather underwhelming and doesn’t feel like a good value at all.  It sparked a conversation around Chick-fil-A and copyright / product copying.  Since Henry had McDonald’s ever put a sandwich in a bag as a wrapper?  Or butter & pickles on the chicken sandwich?  It’s a knock off of the Chick-fil-A chicken sandwich, except about $1 more.  Let’s improve!  This location was actually great though.  The staff was super helpful in explaining the differences of all the new menu items, which is rare for a fast food drive thru worker to be so patient.  Major props.
